#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:581
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&GNU;/&Linux;, FreeBSD and other systems that run X-Windows have multiple "
#| "desktops. You typically have four different desktops installed by "
#| "default. Each desktop can display its own set of programs and files. When "
#| "&kde; first starts up, the desktop you see is Desktop 1. If you press "
